humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that there is one positive lymph node out of ten assessed lymph nodes (1/10). This corresponds to N1 stage according to the AJCC staging system (New Rule 12: N1 indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes). The report also mentions that there are nine negative lymph nodes (0/9), but the final N stage is determined by the most advanced category (in this case, 1/10).

humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient has one out of ten examined lymph nodes with metastatic carcinoma (1/10), as stated in the report. This corresponds to an N1 stage, as defined by the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) staging system for breast cancer.
